ms.ipp.iterable

Class FilteredIterable<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ms.ipp.iterable.FilteredIterable<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public class FilteredIterable<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<T>
    A Decorator for an Iterable<T> which only shows those elements, for which a given filter returns true. The class also accepts an onDelete-hook which is passed on to the iterators it creates (see CustomDeleteIterator for more details).
    Author:
    mykhailo.saienko

      • setFilter

        public FilteredIterable<T> setFilter(java.util.function.Supplier<java.util.function.Predicate<? super T>> filter)
        Sets the filter supplier.
        NOTE: The class does not accept Predicates directly, as filters may be stateful (for example, FilteredIterator::distinctByKey(..) creates such a filter). Hence, every created iterator must have its own copy of the filter.
        Parameters:

      • iterator

        public java.util.Iterator<T> iterator()
        If the filter is not null, returns a FilteredIterator with the filter. Additionally, decorates the resulting iterator with the the onDelete-hook if the latter is not null.
        Specified by:

        public java.util.Spliterator<T> spliterator()
